Description:
Because someone was struck by a train during the early-morning hours on the 7 line, a trash collection train that usually runs between the N W and 7 lines before rush hour could not move back to its storage facility and had to hold on an extra track in Astoria. This extra track is what we normally use to put trains stored overnight in service without interrupting in-service trains.

This caused congestion in both directions.

We are now moving this trash collection train back to its storage facility and working to get N W trains back on time.
